    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-05T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-05T03:34:00-05:00" n="591"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2343: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-05T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 7—7:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Stevens:</p>
                <p>My December 3, 5 p.m.<note n="46" xml:id="d591fn46">Not printed.</note>
                    Representative of Chita government states that conference which was to be held
                    at Manchouli has been <pb facs="0736" n="612" xml:id="pg_612"/> called off and
                    in its place the previous negotiations at Peking regarding commercial relations
                    will be resumed. He says that Far Eastern Republic advises that the question of
                    the Chinese Eastern be allowed to rest until after the discussion at the
                    Washington Conference. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
